<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued January 19 at 4:36PM CST until January 19 at 7:00PM CST by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 515 PM CST
FOR SOUTHWESTERN HARRISON...NORTH CENTRAL PANOLA AND NORTHEASTERN
RUSK COUNTIES...
At 436 PM CST, a severe thunderstorm was located over Hallsville, or
11 miles east of Longview, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Longview, Marshall, Hallsville, Nesbitt and Darco.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
